{"0.08":{"start":"0.08","dur":"3.1","text":"[NARRATOR] Top 10 Medical Myths Everyone Believes"},"4.50":{"start":"4.5","dur":"4.02","text":"10. Shot through the heart"},"11.26":{"start":"11.26","dur":"3.6","text":"Pulp Fiction, The Rock, RoboCop."},"14.86":{"start":"14.86","dur":"2.12","text":"Hollywood has perpetuated the lie"},"17.00":{"start":"17","dur":"1.8","text":"that injecting adrenaline straight"},"18.80":{"start":"18.8","dur":"2.72","text":"to the heart will revive dying patients."},"21.52":{"start":"21.52","dur":"3.04","text":"Spoiler: If you stick a needle in your heart,"},"24.56":{"start":"24.56","dur":"1.58","text":"you&#39;ll puncture the muscle"},"26.14":{"start":"26.14","dur":"1.32","text":"and bleed to death."},"27.46":{"start":"27.46","dur":"1.58","text":"You&#39;re also likely to puncture your\nlungs"},"29.04":{"start":"29.04","dur":"2.4","text":"in the process, causing you to suffocate"},"31.44":{"start":"31.44","dur":"2.94","text":"whilst your heart fails."},"34.38":{"start":"34.38","dur":"3.28","text":"The proper approach is to inject medicine"},"37.66":{"start":"37.66","dur":"1.58","text":"intravenously through a patient&#39;s IV line,"},"39.25":{"start":"39.25","dur":"1.78","text":"where it will reach the heart"},"41.03":{"start":"41.03","dur":"2","text":"in less than 1 minute."},"44.58":{"start":"44.58","dur":"4.38","text":"9. We only use 10% of our brains"},"48.96":{"start":"48.96","dur":"2.5","text":"&quot;It is estimated most human beings"},"51.46":{"start":"51.46","dur":"2.72","text":"only use 10% of the brains&#39; capacity&quot;"},"55.44":{"start":"55.44","dur":"2.52","text":"Nope, not true."},"57.96":{"start":"57.96","dur":"2.92","text":"Up to 65% of people believe in this"},"60.88":{"start":"60.88","dur":"2.5","text":"pseudoscience, which originates from"},"63.38":{"start":"63.38","dur":"3","text":"psychologist William James&#39; 1908 book,"},"66.38":{"start":"66.38","dur":"1.68","text":"&#39;The Energies of Men&#39;"},"68.06":{"start":"68.06","dur":"1.06","text":"where he said that"},"69.12":{"start":"69.12","dur":"2.22","text":"&#39;we are making use of only a small part"},"71.35":{"start":"71.349","dur":"2.751","text":"of our mental and physical resources\u2019."},"74.10":{"start":"74.1","dur":"1.96","text":"In fact neurologists have discovered that"},"76.06":{"start":"76.06","dur":"2.9","text":"we really use 100% of our brain."},"78.96":{"start":"78.96","dur":"2.34","text":"Even during sleep, neurons in the brain"},"81.30":{"start":"81.3","dur":"3.02","text":"fire as much as they do in waking hours."},"84.32":{"start":"84.32","dur":"1.54","text":"Even an action as small as"},"85.86":{"start":"85.86","dur":"1.04","text":"clenching your hand"},"86.90":{"start":"86.9","dur":"1.42","text":"requires activity across"},"88.32":{"start":"88.32","dur":"2.56","text":"more than a tenth of your brain&#39;s regions."},"90.88":{"start":"90.88","dur":"2.2","text":"And when nerve cells aren&#39;t used,"},"93.08":{"start":"93.08","dur":"1.7","text":"including those in the brain"},"94.78":{"start":"94.78","dur":"1.8","text":"they degenerate."},"96.58":{"start":"96.58","dur":"0.58","text":"What&#39;s more,"},"97.16":{"start":"97.16","dur":"2.24","text":"if 90% of your brain were removed,"},"99.40":{"start":"99.4","dur":"2.5","text":"it would be the size of a sheep&#39;s brain."},"105.42":{"start":"105.42","dur":"2.88","text":"Eating at night makes you fat"},"108.30":{"start":"108.3","dur":"2.52","text":"Our metabolisms slow down while we sleep,"},"110.84":{"start":"110.84","dur":"1.9","text":"so late night calorie consumption"},"112.74":{"start":"112.74","dur":"2.46","text":"must be stored as fat, right?"},"115.20":{"start":"115.2","dur":"1.32","text":"Well, not really."},"116.52":{"start":"116.52","dur":"0.96","text":"The most important element"},"117.48":{"start":"117.48","dur":"2.46","text":"is the total amount of calories consumed,"},"119.94":{"start":"119.94","dur":"1.98","text":"not when you consume them."},"121.92":{"start":"121.92","dur":"1.96","text":"If you eat a load of chocolate bars,"},"123.88":{"start":"123.88","dur":"2.58","text":"it doesn&#39;t matter if it&#39;s 10am or 10pm."},"126.46":{"start":"126.46","dur":"1.98","text":"If you eat more than the\ndaily-recommended"},"128.44":{"start":"128.44","dur":"1.02","text":"amount of calories"},"129.46":{"start":"129.46","dur":"2.7","text":"then it can be stored as fat."},"132.16":{"start":"132.16","dur":"1.84","text":"But getting a bit hungry in the evenings"},"134.01":{"start":"134.01","dur":"2.85","text":"is not the same as night eating syndrome,"},"136.86":{"start":"136.86","dur":"1.88","text":"an eating disorder that affects between"},"138.74":{"start":"138.74","dur":"2.58","text":"1 and 2% of the population,"},"141.32":{"start":"141.32","dur":"1.36","text":"which causes sufferers"},"142.68":{"start":"142.68","dur":"1.82","text":"to wake in the middle of the night,"},"144.50":{"start":"144.5","dur":"1.86","text":"with the sudden urge to eat,"},"146.36":{"start":"146.36","dur":"2.04","text":"even when they&#39;re not actually hungry."},"148.42":{"start":"148.42","dur":"1.76","text":"Sufferers consume 56%"},"150.18":{"start":"150.18","dur":"1.52","text":"of their daily calories"},"151.70":{"start":"151.7","dur":"2.34","text":"between 8pm and 6am,"},"154.04":{"start":"154.04","dur":"1.64","text":"and the disorder accounts for"},"155.68":{"start":"155.68","dur":"4.42","text":"at least 10% of obesity cases."},"160.11":{"start":"160.11","dur":"3.87","text":"7. Cold weather makes you sick"},"163.98":{"start":"163.98","dur":"2.34","text":"Between 5 and 20% of Americans"},"166.32":{"start":"166.32","dur":"2.04","text":"catch the flu every year,"},"168.36":{"start":"168.36","dur":"1.9","text":"and most of these cases occur between"},"170.26":{"start":"170.26","dur":"1.64","text":"December and February."},"171.90":{"start":"171.9","dur":"1.78","text":"But getting sick isn&#39;t caused"},"173.68":{"start":"173.68","dur":"1.2","text":"by winter weather."},"174.88":{"start":"174.88","dur":"1.42","text":"Tropical regions of the world"},"176.30":{"start":"176.3","dur":"1.72","text":"are not immune to influenza,"},"178.02":{"start":"178.02","dur":"2.5","text":"with outbreaks springing up irregularly"},"180.52":{"start":"180.52","dur":"1.18","text":"throughout the year."},"181.70":{"start":"181.7","dur":"1.24","text":"People in hot countries"},"182.94":{"start":"182.94","dur":"2.04","text":"like the Philippines and Vietnam catch flu"},"184.98":{"start":"184.98","dur":"3.36","text":"in &#39;minimum&#39; temperatures of 21C."},"188.34":{"start":"188.34","dur":"3.7","text":"So cold weather has no direct affect"},"192.04":{"start":"192.04","dur":"2","text":"on viruses, but it does drive us indoors."},"194.04":{"start":"194.04","dur":"1.82","text":"This puts us in close proximity"},"195.86":{"start":"195.86","dur":"1.02","text":"to more people,"},"196.88":{"start":"196.88","dur":"1.62","text":"which enables influenza"},"198.50":{"start":"198.5","dur":"1.67","text":"to spread more quickly"},"200.17":{"start":"200.17","dur":"3.149","text":"and become endemic in a population."},"203.32":{"start":"203.319","dur":"3.791","text":"6. Vitamins are good for you"},"207.11":{"start":"207.11","dur":"1.66","text":"The vitamin supplement industry"},"208.77":{"start":"208.77","dur":"2.01","text":"is worth $90 billion,"},"210.78":{"start":"210.78","dur":"1.72","text":"claiming to protect us from killers"},"212.50":{"start":"212.5","dur":"1.959","text":"like cancer and heart disease."},"214.46":{"start":"214.459","dur":"2.58","text":"But an increasing number of studies are"},"217.04":{"start":"217.04","dur":"1.66","text":"showing that unless you&#39;re elderly or sick,"},"218.70":{"start":"218.7","dur":"2.1","text":"vitamins are ineffective"},"220.80":{"start":"220.8","dur":"1.84","text":"and possibly even dangerous."},"222.64":{"start":"222.64","dur":"1.16","text":"The Food and Drug Administration"},"223.80":{"start":"223.8","dur":"2.16","text":"doesn&#39;t regulate the vitamin industry"},"225.96":{"start":"225.96","dur":"2.1","text":"like it does prescription drugs,"},"228.06":{"start":"228.06","dur":"2.74","text":"which means dosage and product quality vary."},"230.81":{"start":"230.81","dur":"2.21","text":"Too much vitamin E has been proven"},"233.02":{"start":"233.02","dur":"1.38","text":"to increase your chance"},"234.40":{"start":"234.4","dur":"3","text":"of developing cancer by 17%."},"237.40":{"start":"237.4","dur":"2.58","text":"And fat-soluble supplements like vitamin A"},"239.98":{"start":"239.98","dur":"1.5","text":"can cause blindness,"},"241.48":{"start":"241.48","dur":"3.14","text":"cell degeneration, and hair loss."},"244.63":{"start":"244.629","dur":"2.32","text":"5. Sugary foods cause"},"246.95":{"start":"246.949","dur":"2.131","text":"hyperactivity in children."},"249.08":{"start":"249.08","dur":"2.24","text":"The average American child eats"},"251.32":{"start":"251.32","dur":"2.68","text":"32 teaspoons of sugar a day,"},"254.00":{"start":"254","dur":"2.1","text":"but research has found no link whatsoever"},"256.10":{"start":"256.1","dur":"2.76","text":"between sugar and hyperactive behavior."},"258.86":{"start":"258.86","dur":"2.62","text":"The real culprit is the parent."},"261.48":{"start":"261.48","dur":"0.66","text":"In one study,"},"262.14":{"start":"262.14","dur":"1.56","text":"parents who thought their children"},"263.70":{"start":"263.7","dur":"1.32","text":"had been given sugary drinks"},"265.02":{"start":"265.02","dur":"1.74","text":"when they&#39;d actually been given drinks"},"266.76":{"start":"266.76","dur":"1.42","text":"with artificial sweetener"},"268.18":{"start":"268.18","dur":"1.78","text":"falsely observed an increase in"},"269.96":{"start":"269.96","dur":"2.3","text":"hyperactive behavior in their kids and"},"272.26":{"start":"272.26","dur":"3.32","text":"started criticizing them more as a result."},"275.58":{"start":"275.58","dur":"2.08","text":"The myth persists because the usual times"},"277.66":{"start":"277.66","dur":"2.24","text":"when children&#39;s sugar intake increases"},"279.90":{"start":"279.9","dur":"2.02","text":"are times when children are predisposed"},"281.92":{"start":"281.92","dur":"1.28","text":"to be more excitable -"},"283.20":{"start":"283.2","dur":"1.36","text":"like at birthday parties,"},"284.56":{"start":"284.56","dur":"2.32","text":"Christmas and Halloween."},"286.88":{"start":"286.88","dur":"4.32","text":"4. 8 glasses of water"},"291.20":{"start":"291.2","dur":"2.08","text":"In 1945 the United States&#39;"},"293.28":{"start":"293.28","dur":"1.44","text":"Food and Nutrition board"},"294.72":{"start":"294.72","dur":"2.04","text":"stated that adults should consume"},"296.76":{"start":"296.76","dur":"2.82","text":"2.5  liters of water every day"},"299.58":{"start":"299.58","dur":"2.76","text":"and 20% of this comes from our food."},"302.34":{"start":"302.34","dur":"2.52","text":"But that last part got forgotten."},"304.86":{"start":"304.86","dur":"1.26","text":"Studies have since shown"},"306.12":{"start":"306.12","dur":"1.06","text":"that there is no connection"},"307.18":{"start":"307.18","dur":"2.6","text":"between fluid intake and mortality."},"309.78":{"start":"309.78","dur":"3.12","text":"In fact, too much H2O can be lethal."},"312.90":{"start":"312.9","dur":"2.96","text":"66% of the human body consists of water,"},"315.86":{"start":"315.86","dur":"2.2","text":"which we constantly have to replace"},"318.06":{"start":"318.06","dur":"1.6","text":"when it escapes  through our sweat,"},"319.66":{"start":"319.66","dur":"2.82","text":"breath, urination and defecation."},"322.49":{"start":"322.49","dur":"1.78","text":"But aquaholics beware:"},"324.27":{"start":"324.27","dur":"1.19","text":"6 liters of water"},"325.46":{"start":"325.46","dur":"2.4","text":"and you&#39;ll get water poisoning."},"327.86":{"start":"327.86","dur":"1.04","text":"If you drink too much water,"},"328.91":{"start":"328.91","dur":"1.58","text":"the kidneys can&#39;t remove it"},"330.49":{"start":"330.49","dur":"1.15","text":"from the body and"},"331.64":{"start":"331.64","dur":"1.78","text":"this lowers salt concentrations"},"333.42":{"start":"333.42","dur":"0.8","text":"in the blood."},"334.22":{"start":"334.22","dur":"2.26","text":"This causes the brain to swell,"},"336.48":{"start":"336.48","dur":"1.42","text":"which impairs breathing"},"337.90":{"start":"337.9","dur":"2.08","text":"and causes organ failure."},"339.98":{"start":"339.98","dur":"3.88","text":"3. Cracking your knuckles gives you arthritis"},"343.86":{"start":"343.86","dur":"2.38","text":"This relieving habit stretches the joints"},"346.24":{"start":"346.24","dur":"1.68","text":"and stimulates nerve endings"},"347.92":{"start":"347.92","dur":"2.18","text":"and 54% of us do it."},"350.10":{"start":"350.1","dur":"1.56","text":"When we crack our knuckles,"},"351.66":{"start":"351.66","dur":"1.9","text":"we expand the space between our bones,"},"353.56":{"start":"353.56","dur":"2.72","text":"causing it to fill up with gas bubbles."},"356.28":{"start":"356.28","dur":"1.58","text":"As the joints contract,"},"357.86":{"start":"357.86","dur":"1.98","text":"synovial fluid rushes in"},"359.84":{"start":"359.84","dur":"1.8","text":"and pops these bubbles,"},"361.64":{"start":"361.64","dur":"1.72","text":"causing a loud clicking sound."},"363.36":{"start":"363.36","dur":"2.42","text":"But studies have found no proof that"},"365.78":{"start":"365.78","dur":"1.54","text":"finger-popping increases"},"367.32":{"start":"367.32","dur":"1.61","text":"the risk of arthritis."},"368.93":{"start":"368.93","dur":"2.34","text":"One Californian doctor called Donald Unger"},"371.27":{"start":"371.27","dur":"2.89","text":"conducted a self-experiment for 60 years,"},"374.16":{"start":"374.16","dur":"1.66","text":"where he repeatedly cracked the knuckles"},"375.82":{"start":"375.82","dur":"1.18","text":"on his left hand,"},"377.00":{"start":"377","dur":"2.56","text":"while leaving his right knuckles uncracked."},"379.56":{"start":"379.56","dur":"1.56","text":"The results?"},"381.12":{"start":"381.12","dur":"1.16","text":"Unger reported that"},"382.28":{"start":"382.28","dur":"2.3","text":"&#39;there is not the slightest sign"},"384.58":{"start":"384.58","dur":"2","text":"of arthritis in either hand&#39;."},"386.92":{"start":"386.92","dur":"2.42","text":"2. Hair of the dog"},"389.34":{"start":"389.34","dur":"1.54","text":"In ancient Scotland it was thought"},"390.88":{"start":"390.88","dur":"1.18","text":"that a rabid dog bite"},"392.06":{"start":"392.06","dur":"1.94","text":"could be cured by applying"},"394.00":{"start":"394","dur":"2.44","text":"some of the dog&#39;s hairs to the wound."},"396.44":{"start":"396.44","dur":"1.58","text":"By the mid-sixteenth century,"},"398.02":{"start":"398.02","dur":"1.06","text":"this old wives&#39; tale"},"399.08":{"start":"399.08","dur":"2","text":"was attributed to hangovers"},"401.08":{"start":"401.08","dur":"2.32","text":"and today it&#39;s inspired many cocktails,"},"403.40":{"start":"403.4","dur":"1.5","text":"including the Bloody Mary"},"404.90":{"start":"404.9","dur":"1.72","text":"and Corpse Reviver."},"406.62":{"start":"406.62","dur":"2.1","text":"One modern theory is that hangovers are"},"408.72":{"start":"408.72","dur":"1.44","text":"actually symptoms of"},"410.16":{"start":"410.16","dur":"1.96","text":"mild methanol poisoning,"},"412.12":{"start":"412.12","dur":"2.02","text":"and that another alcoholic drink distracts"},"414.14":{"start":"414.14","dur":"2.62","text":"the body from breaking down methanol,"},"416.77":{"start":"416.77","dur":"2.34","text":"so that it can focus on"},"419.11":{"start":"419.11","dur":"1.89","text":"alcohol&#39;s main component, ethanol."},"421.00":{"start":"421","dur":"1","text":"But most experts agree"},"422.00":{"start":"422","dur":"1.22","text":"that downing more alcohol"},"423.22":{"start":"423.22","dur":"1.1","text":"after a heavy night"},"424.32":{"start":"424.32","dur":"2.8","text":"simply delays the symptoms of a hangover"},"427.12":{"start":"427.12","dur":"2.68","text":"and might even make it worse."},"429.81":{"start":"429.81","dur":"3.32","text":"1. Swallowed gum takes 7 years"},"433.13":{"start":"433.13","dur":"2.22","text":"to pass through your digestive system."},"435.35":{"start":"435.35","dur":"2.18","text":"Doctors have occasionally reported"},"437.53":{"start":"437.53","dur":"2.5","text":"finding gum in patients&#39; digestive tracts,"},"440.03":{"start":"440.03","dur":"1.7","text":"but these pieces are never more than"},"441.73":{"start":"441.73","dur":"1.33","text":"1 week old."},"443.06":{"start":"443.06","dur":"2.1","text":"Chewing gum consists of sweetener,"},"445.16":{"start":"445.16","dur":"1.72","text":"preservatives, flavoring, and a gum base"},"446.88":{"start":"446.88","dur":"2.84","text":"made from synthetic or natural rubber."},"449.72":{"start":"449.72","dur":"1.88","text":"It&#39;s true that gum base"},"451.60":{"start":"451.6","dur":"1.68","text":"is able to withstand stomach acid"},"453.28":{"start":"453.28","dur":"2.34","text":"and intestinal enzymes."},"455.63":{"start":"455.63","dur":"2.02","text":"But provided that the piece of gum"},"457.65":{"start":"457.65","dur":"1.79","text":"is less than 2cm in diameter,"},"459.44":{"start":"459.44","dur":"2.62","text":"our bodies have no problem passing it"},"462.06":{"start":"462.06","dur":"1.8","text":"through our digestive system within"},"463.86":{"start":"463.86","dur":"3.06","text":"6-8 hours. As quickly as any other food."}}